.nh
.TH "TAKO" "1" "Jun 2026" "Tako CLI" "Tako CLI Manual"

.SH NAME
tako-drift - Detect configuration drift


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBtako drift [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Check for drift between your configuration and running services.

.PP
Drift detection compares:
  - Service existence (missing services)
  - Replica counts (services with fewer replicas than expected)
  - Unexpected services (running but not in config)

.PP
Examples:
  # Check once
  tako drift

.PP
# Watch continuously (check every 5 minutes)
  tako drift --watch --interval 5m

.PP
# Watch with notifications
  tako drift --watch --webhook https://hooks.slack.com/...


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for drift

.PP
\fB--interval\fP=5m0s
	Check interval for watch mode

.PP
\fB--watch\fP[=false]
	Continuously watch for drift

.PP
\fB--webhook\fP=""
	Webhook URL for notifications (Slack/Discord/generic)


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--config\fP=""
	config file (default is ./tako.yaml or ./tako.json)

.PP
\fB-e\fP, \fB--env\fP=""
	environment to deploy (default: production or only environment)

.PP
\fB--events\fP=""
	stream progress events to stdout: ndjson (human output moves to stderr)

.PP
\fB--host-key-mode\fP=""
	SSH host key verification mode: tofu, strict, ask (default: tofu)

.PP
\fB--output\fP="text"
	output format: text or json (json reserves stdout for the final result document)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	verbose output


.SH SEE ALSO
\fBtako(1)\fP
